{"comments":"Response Curve and Dynamics Mapping Types.\n\nStatus: PROVEN (proofs/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics.lean)\n\n## Purpose\n\nWhen pressure, tilt, or velocity flows from a stylus, BMI, uploaded mind,\nor AI agent — it passes through response curves that shape the feel.\nThese curves MUST be bounded, monotonic, and sensitivity-tracked.\n\n## Strong Invariants (Proven in Lean4)\n\n1. BOUNDS PRESERVATION — Curves map [0,1] → [0,1]\n2. ENDPOINT PRESERVATION — Curves pass through (0,0) and (1,1)\n3. MONOTONICITY — Curves are monotonically non-decreasing\n4. SENSITIVITY BOUNDS — Each curve has finite maximum derivative\n5. GRADE DEGRADATION — Applying a curve degrades certainty\n6. OUTPUT RANGE VALIDITY — Mapped values land in [valueAtMin, valueAtMax]\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show)\n- Schema.Bounded (UnitInterval)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[83,3]},"title":"Linear"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,9],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[84,3]},"title":"Soft"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[85,9],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[85,3]},"title":"Firm"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[86,3]},"title":"SCurve"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[87,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[87,3]},"title":"Logarithmic"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[88,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[88,3]},"title":"Exponential"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[90,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[90,1]},"title":"eqResponseCurve"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[91,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[91,1]},"title":"ordResponseCurve"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[99,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[93,1]},"title":"showResponseCurve"}],"comments":"Response curve types for dynamics mapping.\n\nEach curve is a function [0,1] → [0,1] with specific feel:\n\n- **Linear**: Direct 1:1 mapping. f(t) = t\n- **Soft**: Light touch sensitive, power < 1. f(t) = sqrt(t)\n- **Firm**: Requires force, power > 1. f(t) = t²\n- **SCurve**: Smooth acceleration/deceleration. f(t) = 3t² - 2t³\n- **Logarithmic**: Quick ramp then plateau. f(t) = log(1 + 9t) / log(10)\n- **Exponential**: Slow start, fast finish. f(t) = (e^t - 1) / (e - 1)\n\nProven: All curves are bounded, monotonic, and pass through (0,0) and (1,1).\nException: Soft maps 0 → sqrt(epsilon) to bound sensitivity.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[88,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[82,1]},"title":"ResponseCurve"},{"children":[],"comments":"All available response curves.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[102,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[102,1]},"title":"allResponseCurves"},{"children":[],"comments":"Human-readable description of each response curve.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[106,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[106,1]},"title":"responseCurveDescription"},{"children":[],"comments":"Maximum sensitivity (derivative bound) for each curve type.\n\nThis bounds error amplification through the curve.\nProven: All sensitivities are <= 8.\n\n| Curve       | Derivative           | Max on [0,1] or [ε,1] |\n|-------------|----------------------|------------------------|\n| Linear      | 1                    | 1                      |\n| Soft        | 1/(2√t)             | 8 (at t = 1/256)       |\n| Firm        | 2t                   | 2                      |\n| SCurve      | 6t - 6t²            | 1.5 (at t = 0.5)       |\n| Logarithmic | 9/((1+9t)·ln(10))   | 3.91 (at t = 0)        |\n| Exponential | e^t/(e-1)           | 1.58 (at t = 1)        |\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[127,55],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[127,1]},"title":"responseCurveMaxSensitivity"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["curve",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"ResponseCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["valueAtMin",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"UnitInterval"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["valueAtMax",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"UnitInterval"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[151,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[147,25]},"title":"DynamicsMapping"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[153,56],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[153,1]},"title":"eqDynamicsMapping"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[160,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[155,1]},"title":"showDynamicsMapping"}],"comments":"A dynamics mapping configuration.\n\nMaps input ∈ [0,1] to output ∈ [valueAtMin, valueAtMax] via curve:\n  output = lerp(valueAtMin, valueAtMax, curve(input))\n\nUsed for pressure→size, tilt→opacity, velocity→flow, etc.\n\nInvariant (enforced at construction): valueAtMin <= valueAtMax\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[151,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[147,1]},"title":"DynamicsMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"Identity mapping: linear curve, full range [0,1].\nInput passes through unchanged.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[164,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[164,1]},"title":"identityMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"Constant mapping: any input produces the same output.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Bounded"],"UnitInterval"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[172,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[172,1]},"title":"constantMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"Soft mapping: light touch sensitive, full range [0,1].\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[180,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[180,1]},"title":"softMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"Firm mapping: requires pressure, full range [0,1].\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[188,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[188,1]},"title":"firmMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"S-curve mapping: smooth transition, full range [0,1].\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[196,33],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[196,1]},"title":"sCurveMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"Logarithmic mapping: quick ramp then plateau, full range [0,1].\nGood for calligraphy — responsive to initial touch, then plateaus.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[205,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[205,1]},"title":"logarithmicMapping"},{"children":[],"comments":"Exponential mapping: slow start, fast finish, full range [0,1].\nGood for building momentum — requires commitment to reach full effect.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Dynamics","Types"],"DynamicsMapping"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[214,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Dynamics/Types.purs","start":[214,1]},"title":"exponentialMapping"}],"name":"Hydrogen.Schema.Brush.Dynamics.Types","reExports":[]}